In the end you end up with something that's somehow worse than the basic lindy candles you started from, one step forward two steps back. While you alternatively could have had perfectly calibrated deep orange hue incandescent light bulbs with no flicker and a use life of decades

Light bulbs are such a good example of how non-linear progress is. Great invention that benefits mankind and then they immediately come up with planned obsolence Phoebus cartel design to lower its quality, then replace it with blue light flickering LEDs that fuck your inner clock

Progesterone and progestins are another one. You find what is essentially a miracle hormone that does everything and proceed to produce worse patentable versions of it with tons of side effects. Sometimes things don't improve but just turn worse with time. It's never that linear.
